			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001149_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'--> 
<!--Hand 01 22 top left--><!--hand 02 63010 top right-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>50 Albemarle <choice><abbr>St.</abbr><expan>Street</expan></choice></placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">7 <choice><abbr>Dec<hi rend="sup">r</hi></abbr><expan>December</expan></choice> 1857</p>
<lb/><p>Sir</p>
<lb/><p>The company which 
<lb/>was attempted to be 
<lb/>formed at Lisbon 
<lb/>on the plan of the 
<lb/>East India Company 
<lb/>did not <choice><sic>recieve</sic><corr>receive</corr></choice> the 
<lb/>sanction of the 
<lb/>Portuguese Government 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001149_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>It was concocted by 
<lb/>a gentleman who 
<lb/>is reported to have 
<lb/>been a little "cracked" 
<lb/>but the main idea 
<lb/>commended itself 
<lb/>to many as feasible 
<lb/>The numbers that 
<lb/>supported him 
<lb/>in bringing it 
<lb/>before the govern
<lb/>ment shewed anxiety 
<lb/>to get the country 
<lb/>off their hands 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001149_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>but a pretty evident 
<lb/>desire also to 
<lb/>secure the ultimate 
<lb/>benefits of English 
<lb/>capital &amp; commercial 
<lb/>enterprise to Portugal 
<lb/>alone. In returning 
<lb/>my great desire 
<lb/>is to get the Zambesi 
<lb/>proclaimed a free 
<lb/>pathway to the country 
<lb/>beyond their possession 
<lb/>They will derive 
<lb/>benefit thereby but 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001149_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'--> 
<lb/>it remains to be seen 
<lb/>whether the Portuguese 
<lb/>Government is 
<lb/>enlightened enough to 
<lb/>see their own 
<lb/>interest. If free passage 
<lb/>is granted frankly 
<lb/>then there is little doubt 
<lb/>but that the Interior 
<lb/>will be opened to 
<lb/>trade &amp; civilization</p>
<lb/><p>The work of <persName>S<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi>
<lb/>Botelho</persName> with which you 
<lb/>are no doubt acquainted 
<lb/>gives a very glowing account 
<lb/>of the resources of East Africa</p>
<lb/><p>I am &amp;c David Livingstone</p>
			
